# Google Drive Link Placeholder

This file helps you track where to add the Google Drive link for RedMet data.

## Steps to Complete:

1. Share the folder on Google Drive:
   - Go to: drive.google.com
   - Navigate to: My Drive > 03_Consulting > dissertation_data > redmet
   - Right-click > Share > "Anyone with the link" > Viewer
   - Copy the link

2. Replace "YOUR_GOOGLE_DRIVE_LINK_HERE" in these files:

   ✏️ data/README.md (line ~10)
   ✏️ code/python/preprocessing/README.md (line ~85)
   ✏️ README.md (line ~153)

3. Search and replace:
   ```bash
   cd ~/GitHub/urban-heat-mexico-city
   grep -r "YOUR_GOOGLE_DRIVE_LINK_HERE" .
   ```

4. After updating, delete this file:
   ```bash
   rm .google-drive-link-placeholder
   ```

5. Commit the changes:
   ```bash
   git add -A
   git commit -m "Add Google Drive link for RedMet historical data"
   git push
   ```

## Example Link Format:

Your link will look like:
https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX?usp=sharing
